<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n42047d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n42" href="#n42047d">N42 (VI.B.31)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n42all.htm#n42047d"> 47(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Abraham&apos;s stone / Ishael&apos;s tomb ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Here was <mark>Abraham&apos;s stone</mark>, and that other which marked <mark>the tomb of Ishmael</mark>, and hard by was Zemzem, the God-sent spring which gushed from the sand when the forefather of the Arabs was perishing of thirst. <small> Stanley Lane-Poole, <a name="SLPS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SLPS"><cite title="source">The Speeches and Table-Talk of the Prophet Mohammad</cite></a> (1882) xxi</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
